    <div class="container" id="overview">
      <div class="breaker"> </div>
      <div class="starter-template">
        <div class="page-header">
          <h2>Overview</h2>
        </div>


<p class="lead">A national program of public health surveillance is being implemented in 269 sites across Jordan.</p>

<p class="lead">The project introduces case-based, integrated disease surveillance that is coded according to the International Classification of Disease (ICD-10).</p>

<p class="lead">The clinician uses the system within the consultation, which introduces clinical-decision support, as well as best practice prescribing guidance and and real-time reporting of information. </p>

<p class="lead">Information is made available within one hour via an online framework with automated generation of SMS and email alerts and support for mapping and reporting, that is accessed at all levels of the Ministry of Health.</p>

<p class="lead">You can sign up to receive weekly epidemiological reports and updates <a target="_blank" href="http://who.us6.list-manage.com/subscribe?u=db2beeeb47818eb521747f4cf&id=d2a4eae0aa">here</a>.</p>


      </div>
<div class="breaker"> </div>
    </div>

<!--<div class="container" id="about">
      <div class="breaker"> </div>
      <div class="starter-template">
        <div class="page-header">
          <h1>About</h1>
        </div>
        <p class="lead">The Ukrainian health system was already weak in the East of the country before the current crisis and is now collapsing in areas of conflict and population displacement.</p>

<p class="lead">Around 1.4 million people are considered to be highly vulnerable and in need of humanitarian assistance in Eastern Jordan. There is insufficient provision of emergency medical services, including trained first-aid personnel and ambulances as well as intensive care and surgical services including specialised trauma, orthopaedics and burns units.</p>

<p class="lead">Primary health care services are also disrupted, with an increasing lack of medical supplies and human resources. The average vaccination coverage in the country remains under 50%, and around 80% of health care workers have fled the fighting areas or died. As the crisis continues, morbidity is likely to increase from untreated and poorly managed non-communicable diseases including diabetes and hypertension, as well as mental health and gender-based violence. Referral services for chronic diseases including TB and HIV will be disrupted and patients may be lost from care.</p>

<p class="lead">As population displacement increases, vulnerable population groups including women and children, elderly and disabled, and minority groups including the Roma will be affected disproportionately.</p>


<p class="lead">The ongoing crisis has had a direct effect on the health of the population, resulting in trauma Adequate emergency medical services, including well equipped ambulances, trained first-aid personnel and health workforce, intensive care, surgeries, burn units, as well as medications and consumables, are insufficient and their immediate availability is a top priority. </p>
      </div>

